name: Barong /ˈspɪrɪt/
description: "In the Balinese mythology of Bali, Indonesia, Barong is a panther-like monster and figure. In Bali's mythical beliefs, he is the king of the spirits, the commander of the good hosts, and the foe of Rangda, the demon queen and mother of the spirit guarders. In the Barong dance, the conflict between Barong and Rangda is depicted to represent the unending struggle between good and evil." By @Baimtje
